FBIS4-53479 "dreas097_d_94014" FBIS-EAS-94-097 Daily Report 18 May 1994 South Korea Argentine Economic Minister Urges ROK Investment Argentine Economic Minister Urges ROK Investment SK1805014994 Seoul YONHAP in English 0119 GMT 18 May 94 SK1805014994 Seoul YONHAP English BFN [Text] Seoul, May 18, (YONHAP) -- Argentine Economic Minister Domingo Cavallo, saying that the business climate in his country is favorable, urged South Korean businessmen to invest in Argentina. "Now is a good time for Korean business enterprises to invest in Argentina," Cavallo told a press conference held Tuesday at Hyatt Hotel in Seoul. Argentina's economy is opening up speedily with 90 percent of state-run companies having been privatized, he said, adding: "In particular, we welcome Korean investment in automobile and electronics sectors." Earlier in the day, Cavallo and Korean Vice Foreign Minister Hong Sun-yong signed an investment guarantee agreement. He also met with leaders of Korean business groups including Hyundai, Samsung, Daewoo and Lucky-Goldstar and asked them to invest more in the South American country.
